      "content": "Escrow, in this real estate context, is essentially a temporary holding account managed by a neutral third party, like a lawyer or a title company. It's where funds—like your down payment or closing costs—are placed until all the conditions of the sale are met. You need it because it protects both you and the seller; it ensures that money is only released once the property transfer is legally complete. This system keeps the transaction secure and orderly.",
